CFT(Cloud Formation Template), ARM(AZURE Resource Manager), Openstack (on-premises) are Infrastructure As Code

Terraform is API As Code is a concept which interacts with any cloud provider using API
API is a application program Interface, which interacts with API  programmatically.



Terraform <------------> TerraformProvider <-------------> Target API


- Manage any Infrastructure
- Track your Infrastructure
- Automate Changes
- Standard Configuration
- Collaborate



write: Define Infrastructure in configuration files

Plan(Dry Run): Review the changes Terraform will make to your infrastructure.

Terraform Apply: Terraform provisions your infrastructure and updates the state file.
you should always store the state file remotely not in local and git

